namedLocations.description: Arial, sometimes marketed as Arial MT, is a sans-serif typeface and computer font packaged with Microsoft Windows, other Microsoft software applications, Apple Mac OS X, and many PostScript computer printers. The typeface was designed in 1982 by Robin Nicholas and Patricia Saunders for Monotype Typography. Arial is also a typeface family comprising standard Arial (Arial Std) and variants, including Arial Black, Bold, Extra Bold, Condensed, Italic, Light, Medium, Monospaced, Narrow, and Rounded.

namedLocations.description: A caudex (plural: caudices) of a plant is a stem, but the term is also used to mean a rootstock and particularly a basal stem structure from which new growth arises. In the strict sense of the term, meaning a stem, "caudex" is most often used with plants that have a different stem morphology from the typical angiosperm dicotyledon stem: examples of this include palms, ferns, and cycads.

transcript.text: Welcome to on Print shop.
In this video we will learn about template properties master.
Let's talk about key features and benefits.
It helps you to create master properties like fonts, color, images, template form fields, month layout and assign them to as many templates as required.
It reduce your effort in creating separate template properties.
You can easily filter out the template properties with respect to their types.
Let's have a look into the admin.
First of all, we need to go to templates.
Click on Template properties master.
Here you can see all your template properties master created.
So to add a new template properties master click on add button.
So here you can put the property title.
Suppose font select the store whether you want to set for a default store as a user type and then select the type of property you want to create.
So I'm taking over here font.
So you can select all the fonts which you want to show into a template only.
So suppose these six fonts I want to show into a property.
So after saving it here we can see there is a template properties master created.
So this we can use into any template.
So let's go to a template, just click on action, click on template properties.
And here we can see template properties master to choose.
And here we can select from the drop down the template properties available.
And here you can see the fonts.
So when we save it and we click on preview.
So in the designer studio as you can see when we select a font then here only those fonts are coming which we have selected into the template properties master.
So in this way you can create template properties master for colour as well.
So to add a colour just click on add button, put the property title, select the store select type.
Here we are taking colours just click on add button, choose the colour coding.
So here you can see we can add N number of colours and justice.
Click on saving back and then just go to the Template properties master.
Click on colours, select Template Properties master and choose the template property master we created.
So only these three colours will be visible.
And now let's go to the storefront and we refresh the page.
So now in the text you can see only those three selected colours are coming to choose.
So in this way you can create template properties master in your store.
Thank you for watching this video.
In case of any further concern, feel free to connect with us.
